column5: Regarding Brain B's post about his fuel consumption, here's one you ain't gonna believe, no way, no how. According to my GPS here's my top speed achieved, and average speed. Not bad for a 2007 Mazda 6 wagon.
Just for fun, I left my portable GPS turned on in my suitcase when I went to the airport one time...my max speed is now 850 km/h!!
NICE!!! I see you got the turbo!!!!

I love the thing, but it does some crazy stuff. It seems to have a bit of a blind spot up on Horseshoe valley Road, sometimes it will indicate that I'm half a kilometre into the south fields and a few hundred metres below sea level.
How did the tires hold up to that kind of speed? LOL
